00:34:07,801 --> 00:34:09,522
from the heart of the team, from its people.

787
00:34:11,883 --> 00:34:14,204
I like how we all randomly picked like four lessons

788
00:34:14,244 --> 00:34:14,884
for everybody to learn.

789
00:34:16,145 --> 00:34:16,745
Producers here.

790
00:34:19,804 --> 00:34:22,406
I always love this quote by Peter Drucker, right?

791
00:34:22,426 --> 00:34:24,568
That culture eats strategy for breakfast.

792
00:34:25,308 --> 00:34:28,511
And when we looked at teams that really thrived at RStudio,

793
00:34:28,551 --> 00:34:32,714
it wasn't because of process or schedule or best practices.

794
00:34:33,055 --> 00:34:35,136
It was kind of these cultural norms on the team.

795
00:34:35,457 --> 00:34:37,679
And not just the team leadership, but the entire team.

796
00:34:38,699 --> 00:34:40,421
And when we tried to replicate those,

