00:36:11,994 --> 00:36:14,256
focus in on if you can't build consensus,

832
00:36:14,416 --> 00:36:16,537
at least commit to the group, commit to the team.

833
00:36:17,137 --> 00:36:20,218
And by doing that, a lot of times they were able to eliminate a lot of the,

834
00:36:20,518 --> 00:36:25,200
well, I told you so, right, out there in the future, or people sabotaging the team

835
00:36:25,240 --> 00:36:28,461
because they didn't feel like they ever bought into the decision.

836
00:36:28,561 --> 00:36:31,662
So people that were willing to acknowledge and say their disagreement,

837
00:36:31,722 --> 00:36:35,343
but then commit to each other as a team, were much more powerful teams.

838
00:36:38,918 --> 00:36:41,500
So the second cultural attribute we noticed a lot

839
00:36:42,080 --> 00:36:44,301
was the teams had really good strategies

